ce:section.ce:para:
In order to test its potential in practical application, stability of RTP-TP for trace water detection have also been analyzed in Fig. 5
                        . An RTP-TP was firstly immersed in ethanol for 1 min and then taken out and continuously irradiated by a UV lamp (365 nm, 12W) for 60 min. No significant decrease in RTP intensity of as-treated RTP-TP was found in Fig. 5a, indicating the satisfactory stability of RTP-TP samples. Repeatability test of RTP-TP is also indispensable before practical application. Herein, ten pieces of RTP-TP were used to detect anhydrous ethanol (black) and then they were applied for trace water detection in ethanol (4 v/v-%, red) (Fig. 5b). The RSD (relative standard deviation) of the ten groups of experiment is 2.07%, such a small RSD value implies that the RTP-TP has high precision and excellent repeatability. Furthermore, the RTP-RP was applied in real organic solvents samples. Two samples of commercial ethanol with different concentrate of water (2% and 4%, Table 1
                        ) were used to determine the recovery rate of water detection for RTP-TP. The ratio of the difference between the detected concentration and the spiked concentration is defined as the recovery rate. As expected, the recovery of RTP-TP for detection trace water in commercial ethanol is 101.5%.
